-- Virginia sues 13 banks for $1 bln over alleged mortgage bond fraud 
-- By Aruna Viswanatha
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 12:42PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Sept 16 (Reuters) - The state of Virginia sued units of Barclays Plc <BARC.L>, Citigroup Inc <C.N>, and 11 other banks, accusing them of defrauding the state's retirement fund by selling it shoddy mortgage bonds, Virginia Attorney General Mark Herring said on Tuesday.

